";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"https://yithemes.com/?p=795446\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:328:\"There is an unwritten rule for those who try to boost the sales in their online store: if a marketing tool gets a name that defines it, then it works. Reading “This exploits the Cross Selling method” rather then “Combines the sale of several related products in order to increase the average cart value” sounds [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Andrea Presenti\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11676:\"<p dir=\"ltr\">There is an unwritten rule for those who <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tag/sales/\">try to boost the sales in their online store</a>: if a marketing tool gets a name that defines it, then it works.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Reading “This exploits the Cross Selling method” rather then “Combines the sale of several related products in order to increase the average cart value” sounds indeed better and more professional.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This doesn’t mean that other methods don’t work, but seeing the same results come up in our “How to increase sales on my e-commerce store” researches time and time again increases our trust in a specific method.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">But if a marketing tool got its own specific name that defines it, then it might be too complex for inexperienced users, making the first approach to it harder.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>And this is the case for Cross Selling and Up Selling</strong>.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">If like me, you searched the internet for miracle ways to boost the sales in your store before, then I’m sure this isn’t the first time you hear these words, so why not shed some light on how these two marketing tools work? And why not see how to use them on your e-commerce store?</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Cross selling: sell more items to the same customer</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Of the many variables that affect the income in an online store, one of them is more important than the others: the average customer value.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">While it’s important for any store to <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/how-maxs-customer-was-able-to-improve-the-conversion-rate-on-his-digital-products-by-25/\">increase the number of customers</a> and the overall conversion rate, if we manage to also boost the average amount of money spent by each single customer, we would greatly improve the average value of every single transaction.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>These two methods are directly involved in this point: meaning how to increase the value of each single customer.</em></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Their effectiveness is easily explained: imagine having 100 customers who spend an average of $50 on your website, your gross income would amount to $5000.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">If you’d manage to increase their expenses from $50 to $70 each, you would gain $2000 with the very same number of customers.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">So how does Cross Selling work?</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Cross selling has the goal of encouraging customers to purchase several products at the same time, thus <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/increase-sales-thanks-to-discounts-part-1/\">increasing your average purchase value</a>.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">It’s generally more effective in case of products that you can sell as bundles, such as a camera and its casing, memory card, lenses, etc etc. But it may also be used in different fields such as clothing (shirt + trousers) <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/free-themes/the-polygon-the-ultimate-e-commerce-wordpress-theme-for-gamers/\">videogames </a>(game + expansion or related game), food (meal + dips + sides), so it can basically apply to any kind of product.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This marketing tool owes its effectiveness to proposing these items to customers who would be interested to purchase those accessories anyway but didn’t consider getting them from your store, such as the camera and its casing.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Customers often don’t realize they are going to need other products as well as the one they are buying and their interest might be raised by offering them similar products to the one they are after (which they are more likely to appreciate).</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>So, now that this technique’s effectiveness has been established, how can we apply a Cross Selling system to our store?</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">WooCommerce itself comes in handy in this, offering us the opportunity to link a product to others, that are going to be displayed at the bottom of a product’s landing page.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This function, however useful, is also imperfect and less than functional, given that very few customers reach down to that section and even less are going to be interested in clicking related products (so just immagine how many of them will actually reach the checkout page).</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">So how should we do this? Well, we can get inspired by the big names in the field, such as Amazon!</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">If you ever purchased from Amazon you must have noticed how related products are constantly proposed, as well as the “Frequently Bought Together”</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">They are displayed underneath any product, showing a sort of product bundle which encourages customers to purchase more items at the same time!</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-795447\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/freqBoughtTogether.png\" alt=\"freqBoughtTogether\" width=\"739\" height=\"201\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/freqBoughtTogether.png 739w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/freqBoughtTogether-300x82.png 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/freqBoughtTogether-382x104.png 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/freqBoughtTogether-270x73.png 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 739px) 100vw, 739px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">It’s a working system, both thanks to the reasons I have listed so far, and because it uses a weakness into our customers’ psychology. Neuromarketing uses an unconscious process called “Principle os Social Proof” which states that, in short, if a product or action is purchased/done by many people, that product/action acquires value.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">So just stating two items are “Frequently Bought Together” brings our customers to purchase more products, since unconsciously it’s as if they were reading “Others bought these items togher, I should do the same thing”.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Pro tip: if you use WooCommerce for your online store, you can easily introduce this function thanks to the <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-frequently-bought-together/\">WooCommerce Frequently Bought Together</a> plugin.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Clearly this is one of the most effective ways to incentivate Cross Selling, but you don’t have to necessarily display your products so bluntly. For instance, during the purchase proces, it could be interesting to display related products to the one that was added to the cart, in a pop-up window, making them look as a friendly advice rather than an attempt to sell more products.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-795448\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/related.jpg\" alt=\"related\" width=\"696\" height=\"636\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/related.jpg 696w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/related-300x274.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/related-382x349.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/related-150x137.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 696px) 100vw, 696px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Pro tip: you can integrate this function to your WooCommerce store thanks to the <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-added-to-cart-popup/\">YITH WooCommerce Added to Cart Pop-up</a> plugin.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">So, for short, Cross Selling is the ideal technique for those who sell many different related items…  But what if instead of selling several products, we want to bring the customer to purchase the most expensive ones?</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This is when Up Selling comes into play.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Up Selling: let your customers pick your most expensive service</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Despite Cross Selling is indeed effective, it may not apply to just any store, especially in case of stores which sell few very expensive products (such as a car shop, a jewelry shop, a digital products store etc…).</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">How is it different from the first tool? While Cross Selling brings customers to increase their average expense by adding more products to the cart, Up Selling aims for the single purchase, but with a higher value.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">For this reason Up Selling is the ideal technique for those who own a store in which multiple purchase are rare.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Let’s take for instance a jewelry store: the vendors are offering a pendant, they could try to push customers towards a more expensive pendant, maybe including a more rare and valuable stone in it, so that if that works, they would have significantly increased the value and the expenses of a given customer.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Let’s consider some more extreme cases: a car shop. Or a website that rents flats: customers will clearly purchase/rent a single product, Cross Selling cannot apply here. But what if we managed to bring them to take interest in a more expensive car or in renting a flat with higher fees? We would increase the value of each single customer, increasing profits from day one.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Ok, so it’s a working technique… but how can we apply it to an online store?</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Up Selling can be a rather tricky technique and it shouldn’t become too obvious (you can’t just go “Hey, people aren’t buying this, you should buy this one instead”) but you can disguise it as a feature you are offering.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Consider a case as this one:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">I’m looking to buy a new laptop. Given this isn’t a regular everyday expense (such as buying the newspaper or having a coffee) I will weigh my purchase carefully, considering the years that will follow.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In this case I’m already keen on spending more than I anticipated, in order to get a product that will not only satisfy me for the time being but also be a durable one.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">A most effective way of bringing customers towards more expensive product is to offer a tool to compare items: such as having to choose between two computers, one of which is more expensive than the other.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">When faced with all the better features included in the higher price computer, since I’m already keen on spending a high amount of money, I might as well go for the most expensive one.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-795449\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/compare.png\" alt=\"compare\" width=\"581\" height=\"473\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/compare.png 581w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/compare-300x244.png 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/compare-382x311.png 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/compare-168x137.png 168w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 581px) 100vw, 581px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Clearly this can apply to all sorts of products, for instance by comparing brands for clothes, smartphones, fragrances etc&#8230;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Pro tip: if you wish to offer an easy way to compare products on your WooCommerce based store, you can use the <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-compare/\">WooCommerce Compare</a> plugin.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In the end I should point out that while these tools are effective on their own, they might as well be combined.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Let’s get back to out computer shop example: Cross Selling is good to sell users a mouse and keyboard together with the pc they’re buying, Up selling will make them choose the most powerful (and expensive) computer.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Try it out yourself and apply these two techniques that will turn every single customer in a little gold mine.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:125:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/cross-selling-and-up-selling-two-techniques-that-will-improve-sales-on-your-website/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"7\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:77:\"WooCommerce: how to sell pizza on delivery creating an automatic order system\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:113:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/woocommerce-how-to-sell-pizza-on-delivery-creating-an-automatic-order-system/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:122:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/woocommerce-how-to-sell-pizza-on-delivery-creating-an-automatic-order-system/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Fri, 10 Jun 2016 12:16:22 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"https://yithemes.com/?p=795413\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:303:\"The main rule each marketing system is based on is the rule of supply and offer, which is why if we are dealing in primary goods such as food, you can be sure that it will be generally desirable product. Let’s consider a pizza shop offering a delivery service: it’s a winning idea from the [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Andrea Presenti\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28681:\"<p dir=\"ltr\">The main rule each marketing system is based on is the rule of supply and offer, which is why if we are dealing in primary goods such as food, you can be sure that it will be generally desirable product.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Let’s consider a pizza shop</strong> offering a delivery service: it’s a winning idea from the start since the amount of time people spend having meals gets shorter and shorter, we generally and up having our meals delivered at home.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">A home delivery service owes its effectiveness to three main factors:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>It’s easy.</li>\r\n 	<li>It’s handy.</li>\r\n 	<li>It’s quick.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Anybody can grab their phone and order a pizza, and that’s surely easier than having to personally go to the shop, order it and then collect it.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">We also shouldn’t underestimate the comfort of being able to eat at home without having to get ready to leave the house, face the noise you might find in the pizzeria, hoping to find a free table etc etc&#8230;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">I don’t need to list all the advantages of a home delivery service, if you are reading this article then you already know them well.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">What I’m proposing here is an alternative way to handle these orders so that you could be a step ahead of your competitors. How? Well, by powering up the three advantages I listed earlier!</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\">Many fast foods are replacing the classic ordering system with automatic panels where you can make your selection, why not do the same?</h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>How can we make ordering easier compared to a simple phone call?</strong> Let users do it from their computers, in order for them to be able to order the pizza they want without having to remember their possible choices and prices.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>How can you make ordering easier?</strong> Offer the opportunity to pay by credit card directly on the website, with no need to look for cash, wait for the change back etc&#8230;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>So how do you make the ordering process quicker?</strong> Well, it’s two clicks against one phone call. No match.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">There are, in fact, pizzerias that already offer the chance to order online, but is it possible to take this service one step further?</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In this tutorial we will see how to offer an automated reservation system via WooCommerce in which customers can assemble the pizza they want thanks to a dynamic system that increases or lower the price according to their choices (A similar service to the one offered by PizzaHut and other similar companies).</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Required Plugin</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-product-add-ons/\">YITH WooCommerce Product Add-Ons</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Plugin Settings</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">It’s easy to understand how an e-commerce store is a valid platform to handle an online orders system, creating a catalog including all the available pizzas and then allowing customers to purchase them.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Food, however, and pizzas in particular, are a kind of product which is subject to many variations during the ordering process, which happen according to customers’ taste (with or without tomato sauce, gluten, type of crust and all of the extras it might come with).</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This is the reason why the problem with offering a catalog lies in finding yourself with two choices:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Offering non-customizable pizzas, running the risk of losing part of your customers.</li>\r\n 	<li>Giving them the chance to do so through additional notes, without being able do adjust the price accordingly</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In this tutorial we are going to create a product called &#8220;<b>Create your pizza</b>&#8221; which will allow customers to choose between these options:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><b>Red/White pizza</b></li>\r\n 	<li><b>With gluten/Gluten free</b></li>\r\n 	<li><b>Regular crust/Filled crust</b></li>\r\n 	<li><b>Sauces &amp; Dips</b></li>\r\n 	<li><b>Multiple choice of ingredients</b></li>\r\n 	<li><b>Delivery date</b></li>\r\n 	<li><b>Delivery time</b></li>\r\n 	<li><b>Delivery address</b></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">As you can see, these are a lot of options, but it’s always best to affer a product with as many customization options as possible, in order for customers to find just what they are after.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">We will also set some of these options as free while others will alter the total price.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Let’s see how to create these variations step by step.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">First of all, you need to create the “<b>Create your Pizza</b>” product, the same way you would do with any other WooCommerce product:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-795429\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/pizza-product-1024x395.jpg\" alt=\"pizza-product\" width=\"1024\" height=\"395\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/pizza-product-1024x395.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/pizza-product-300x116.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/pizza-product-768x297.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/pizza-product-382x148.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/pizza-product-270x104.jpg 270w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/pizza-product.jpg 1292w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Once it’s created, this is what it’s going to look like in your store:</p>\r\nhttps://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/pizza-product.jpg\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Once the plugin is installed and activated, you can create the group of additional options you wish to add to the product you have created, by going to <b>Products &gt; Product Add-Ons</b></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The first thing you need to do is deciding the name you wish to assign to the group of customization rules you are going to create. In this case, I’ve called it “<b>Pizza</b>”.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-795424\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-group-pizza.jpg\" alt=\"new-group-pizza\" width=\"855\" height=\"511\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-group-pizza.jpg 855w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-group-pizza-300x179.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-group-pizza-768x459.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-group-pizza-382x228.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-group-pizza-229x137.jpg 229w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 855px) 100vw, 855px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Once you have set the name, you can link the group to single products or whole categories of products. Given that in this case I wish to link it to the product I initially created, I will search for “<b>Create your Pizza</b>” in the “<b>Products</b>” section:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-795425\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-group-product-pizza.jpg\" alt=\"new-group-product-pizza\" width=\"911\" height=\"515\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-group-product-pizza.jpg 911w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-group-product-pizza-300x170.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-group-product-pizza-768x434.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-group-product-pizza-382x216.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-group-product-pizza-242x137.jpg 242w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 911px) 100vw, 911px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Now you can save the group you have created and move on to create the several add-ons you want to insert in the product page, by clicking on <b>Add new</b>:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-795422\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-addons-pizza-1024x517.jpg\" alt=\"new-addons-pizza\" width=\"1024\" height=\"517\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-addons-pizza-1024x517.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-addons-pizza-300x152.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-addons-pizza-768x388.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-addons-pizza-88x45.jpg 88w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-addons-pizza-382x193.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-addons-pizza-270x137.jpg 270w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-addons-pizza.jpg 1077w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">You can create all sorts of variations, as you can see from the drop down menu:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-795423\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-addons-type-pizza.jpg\" alt=\"new-addons-type-pizza\" width=\"962\" height=\"496\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-addons-type-pizza.jpg 962w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-addons-type-pizza-300x155.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-addons-type-pizza-768x396.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-addons-type-pizza-88x45.jpg 88w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-addons-type-pizza-382x197.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/new-addons-type-pizza-266x137.jpg 266w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 962px) 100vw, 962px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">At this point the process is quick and easy, you can create one by one all of the additional options you might need:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>With Tomato / Without Tomato</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Let’s create a “<b>SELECT</b>” kind of field (which will allow customers to chose between several options and call it <b>With Tomato / Without Tomato.</b></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remember to insert a text that will go by your option in the “Option Label” field, otherwise it won’t be displayed in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-795442\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/with-tomato-1024x497.jpg\" alt=\"with-tomato\" width=\"1024\" height=\"497\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/with-tomato-1024x497.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/with-tomato-300x146.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/with-tomato-768x373.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/with-tomato-382x186.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/with-tomato-270x131.jpg 270w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/with-tomato.jpg 1268w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Once saved, the options is going to appear this way in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-795436\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-tomato-1024x561.jpg\" alt=\"product-tomato\" width=\"1024\" height=\"561\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-tomato-1024x561.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-tomato-300x164.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-tomato-768x421.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-tomato-382x209.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-tomato-250x137.jpg 250w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-tomato.jpg 1038w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Gluten Free</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With the increasing number of celiac people, the chance of ordering gluten free pizza became essential for any pizzeria.\r\nI will then create a “<b>Checkbox</b>” customers will be able to check in order to ask for a pizza with no gluten. I will call it <b>Gluten Free</b>.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remember to insert the text that will come with your option in the “Option Label” field or it won’t be displayed in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-795419\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/gluten-free-1024x529.jpg\" alt=\"gluten free\" width=\"1024\" height=\"529\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/gluten-free-1024x529.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/gluten-free-300x155.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/gluten-free-768x397.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/gluten-free-88x45.jpg 88w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/gluten-free-382x198.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/gluten-free-265x137.jpg 265w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/gluten-free.jpg 1056w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And this is how this option will appear in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-795432\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-gluten-1024x459.jpg\" alt=\"product-gluten\" width=\"1024\" height=\"459\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-gluten-1024x459.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-gluten-300x135.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-gluten-768x345.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-gluten-382x171.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-gluten-270x121.jpg 270w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-gluten.jpg 1128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Type of crust</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In case I wish to offer this extra service, I can create a dedicated field for the type of crust my customer’s pizza is going to come with. Just like I did for the tomato sauce, I will create a “<b>Select</b>” field and I will create several possibilities to choose from in <b>Label Options</b>. I have created three of them for this article: <b>Normal</b>, <b>Stuffed</b> and <b>Italian</b>. I also set for the Stuffed crust to cost $2 extra.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remember to insert the text that will come with your option in the “Option Label” field or it won’t be displayed in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-795416\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/crust-1024x627.jpg\" alt=\"crust\" width=\"1024\" height=\"627\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/crust-1024x627.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/crust-300x184.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/crust-768x470.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/crust-382x234.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/crust-224x137.jpg 224w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/crust.jpg 1145w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And this is how this variation is going to be displayed in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-795430\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-crust-1024x561.jpg\" alt=\"product-crust\" width=\"1024\" height=\"561\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-crust-1024x561.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-crust-300x164.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-crust-768x420.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-crust-382x209.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-crust-250x137.jpg 250w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-crust.jpg 1054w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Sauce</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Many services such as the famous PizzaHut offer a selection of sauces and dips that come with the pizza. If this is your case, all you need to do is creating another “<b>Select</b>” field including the several possibilities customers will be able to choose from.\r\nIn my case I will offer three dips: <b>Ketchup</b>, <b>Mustard</b> and <b>BBQ Sauce</b>.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remember to insert the text that will come with your option in the “Option Label” field or it won’t be displayed in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-795438\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/sauce-1024x643.jpg\" alt=\"sauce\" width=\"1024\" height=\"643\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/sauce-1024x643.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/sauce-300x189.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/sauce-768x483.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/sauce-382x240.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/sauce-218x137.jpg 218w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/sauce.jpg 1036w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And this is how this variation is going to be displayed in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-795435\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-sauce-1024x499.jpg\" alt=\"product-sauce\" width=\"1024\" height=\"499\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-sauce-1024x499.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-sauce-300x146.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-sauce-768x374.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-sauce-382x186.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-sauce-270x132.jpg 270w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-sauce.jpg 1047w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Ingredients &#8211; Meats</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">After handling the pizza base, let’s move on to the ingredients. I used the PizzaHut model and divided the ingredients into two types: Meats and Veggies.\r\nOnce more I’ve created a “<b>Select</b>” field including the options customers will be able to choose from.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remember to insert the text that will come with your option in the “Option Label” field or it won’t be displayed in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-795421\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/meat-1024x643.jpg\" alt=\"meat\" width=\"1024\" height=\"643\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/meat-1024x643.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/meat-300x188.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/meat-768x482.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/meat-382x240.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/meat-218x137.jpg 218w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/meat.jpg 1126w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And this is how this variation is going to be displayed in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-795434\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-meat.jpg\" alt=\"product-meat\" width=\"946\" height=\"523\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-meat.jpg 946w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-meat-300x166.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-meat-768x425.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-meat-382x211.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-meat-248x137.jpg 248w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 946px) 100vw, 946px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Ingredients &#8211; Veggies</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">If you wish to offer your customers the chance of ordering a balanced pizza, you can add another “Select” option called Veggies from which they will be able to choose between all of the available vegetables.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remember to insert the text that will come with your option in the “Option Label” field or it won’t be displayed in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-795441\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/veggies-1024x620.jpg\" alt=\"veggies\" width=\"1024\" height=\"620\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/veggies-1024x620.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/veggies-300x182.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/veggies-768x465.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/veggies-382x231.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/veggies-226x137.jpg 226w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/veggies.jpg 1149w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And this is how this option is going to look like in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-795437\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-veggies.jpg\" alt=\"product-veggies\" width=\"837\" height=\"358\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-veggies.jpg 837w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-veggies-300x128.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-veggies-768x328.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-veggies-382x163.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-veggies-270x115.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 837px) 100vw, 837px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Delivery day</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This is a rather optional field, but it might be interesting to offer your customers the chance to order a pizza for the next day, so I will create a “Date” field and call it “Delivery Date”.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remember to insert the text that will come with your option in the “Option Label” field or it won’t be displayed in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-795418\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/delivery-date.jpg\" alt=\"delivery date\" width=\"902\" height=\"469\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/delivery-date.jpg 902w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/delivery-date-300x156.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/delivery-date-768x399.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/delivery-date-88x45.jpg 88w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/delivery-date-382x199.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/delivery-date-263x137.jpg 263w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 902px) 100vw, 902px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And this is what it’s going to look like in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-795431\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-date.jpg\" alt=\"product-date\" width=\"861\" height=\"367\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-date.jpg 861w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-date-300x128.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-date-768x327.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-date-382x163.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-date-270x115.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 861px) 100vw, 861px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Delivery time</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">If the previous field was optional, this one is required to deliver pizzas. Customers must be able to set the time they whish to receive their pizza, so I will create a “<b>Text</b>” field called <b>Delivery Time</b> customers can choose to pick the time they want.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remember to insert the text that will come with your option in the “Option Label” field or it won’t be displayed in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-795420\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/hour.jpg\" alt=\"hour\" width=\"854\" height=\"430\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/hour.jpg 854w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/hour-300x151.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/hour-768x387.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/hour-88x45.jpg 88w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/hour-382x192.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/hour-270x137.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 854px) 100vw, 854px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And this is what this option will look like in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-795433\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-hour.jpg\" alt=\"product-hour\" width=\"811\" height=\"368\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-hour.jpg 811w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-hour-300x136.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-hour-768x348.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-hour-382x173.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-hour-270x123.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 811px) 100vw, 811px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Delivery address</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Now all we have left to do is creating the field that would start our pizza delivery process: the customer’s address.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">So let’s create a “<b>Text Area</b>” field (bigger than the Text field) called <b>Address</b> customers can use to enter their location.\r\nRemember to add the text that will go with the “Option Label” option:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-795414\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/address.jpg\" alt=\"address\" width=\"900\" height=\"456\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/address.jpg 900w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/address-300x152.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/address-768x389.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/address-88x45.jpg 88w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/address-382x194.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/address-270x137.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And this is what this option will look like in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-795415\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/address-product.jpg\" alt=\"address-product\" width=\"746\" height=\"307\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/address-product.jpg 746w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/address-product-300x123.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/address-product-382x157.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/address-product-270x111.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 746px) 100vw, 746px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Now that you filled in all the options, this is what your product will look like:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-795440\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/total-product-1024x738.jpg\" alt=\"total-product\" width=\"1024\" height=\"738\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/total-product-1024x738.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/total-product-300x216.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/total-product-768x553.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/total-product-382x275.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/total-product-190x137.jpg 190w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/total-product.jpg 1180w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And once all the optional choices are added, customers will see their price divided between base price and added options:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"> <img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-795444\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-total.jpg\" alt=\"product-total\" width=\"757\" height=\"382\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-total.jpg 757w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-total-300x151.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-total-88x45.jpg 88w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-total-382x193.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/product-total-270x137.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 757px) 100vw, 757px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This is how you can set up an effective delivery order system in your website in just a few steps, creating an e-commerce store in which payment on delivery is just an alternative to online payment!</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:118:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/woocommerce-how-to-sell-pizza-on-delivery-creating-an-automatic-order-system/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:89:\"Increase sales thanks to discounts: how to use them and which ones you should chose (2/2)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:78:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/increase-sales-thanks-to-discounts-part-2/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/increase-sales-thanks-to-discounts-part-2/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 30 May 2016 11:43:35 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"https://yithemes.com/?p=794548\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:330:\"Although a product was designed specifically for one single function, that doesn’t mean that’s the only thing we can do with it. In my previous article I’ve gone through how we can boost the effectiveness of discounts as a way to increase sales, using them as a part of elaborate marketing schemes. But despite the [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Andrea Presenti\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9514:\"<p dir=\"ltr\">Although a product was designed specifically for one single function, that doesn’t mean that’s the only thing we can do with it.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In my previous article I’ve gone through how we can boost the effectiveness of discounts as a way to increase sales, using them as a part of elaborate marketing schemes.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">But despite the fact that <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tag/sales/\">increasing sales</a> is an important aspect for all vendors, a discount system can bring several different results according to how it’s being used, and that’s just what we are going to talk about today: what alse can discounts be used for, despite increasing sales?</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Let’s see how a simple discount can help us in any single aspect of our e-commerce store:</em></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Increase your customer base</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Increase the conversion rate on your store</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Increase the average customer value</strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Get back to lost customers</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Spread the word about your store</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">We have seen howdiscounts can bring new customers to your store<a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/increase-sales-thanks-to-discounts-part-1/\"> in my previous article</a>, thanks to a loyalty program, but it’s not guaranteed that any store would want or have the chance to offer such a system for their products.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In which case, does discounts get stripped of this function? No, there are several ways to spread the word about your store thanks to offers and/or discounts.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">For instance, we could use the endless potential of social networks, given they are the most populated and comfortable part of the internet for most users.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Sure, having your own working Facebook page is important, but it will always be seen as a seller’s page, so having somebody else sharing our content proves to be more efficient.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">If we’d manage to convince a customer to share our product, we would immeately enter a trusted circle of friends and acquientances, turning every single share in hundreds of potential views.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">But how can we convince our customers to share an item? We could ask them, but we know just how much we are keen to selfless acts, so here’s when discounts come in handy.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Offering discounts in exchange for a share</strong> increases their number and keeps customers coming (in order to use their discount vouchers) which actively spreads the word about our products.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><b>Pro Tip:</b> if you use WooCommerce, you can easily offer discounts in exchange for shares using the <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-share-for-discounts/\">WooCommerce Share for Discounts</a> plugin.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Persuade customers to purchase from your store</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This is usually another sore note for online sellers, we work hard to spread the word about our store and bring new customers to our website, but the conversion rate stays low.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Increasing the conversion rate is the best way to boost sales on your store</strong>, since you “just” need to increase the percentage from 1% to 3% to triple your sales, without having to look for no miracle solution around the web.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">But how do we convince our potential customers to buy from us?</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">One of the most effective ways to get rid of any doubt and persuade customers to purchase is to <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/how-to-encourage-further-purchases-and-increase-the-amount-of-reviews-on-your-e-commerce-store/\">show reviews and proof of quality</a> and reliability from other customers (for the same reason we’ve seen earlier about social networks).</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Why is what other customers think so important? Just like when we talked about the Principle of Scarcity in the previous article, speaking about timed promotions, this time Robert Cialdini comes in handy thanks to another Princple: the Principle of Social Proof.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This principle states that if an item is bought by a big number of people, said object automatically acquires a higher value.  It’s the same psicological process that’s behind fashion or simply why we look at others when we are unsure about how to act.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Given this, it’s easy to understand how important it is to use this Principle in <strong>sales system</strong>: if we manage to prove that a product has been bought and appreciated by many people, then most of our job is already done.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">But it’s always the same issue: <strong>how do we persuade customers to leave reviews?</strong> It’s hard enough to convince them to come back to our store after one purchase, let alone writing a review.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Once again the answer is the same: offer a discount as reward. This way you will increase the number of reviews, which will increase your conversion rate triggering a a cycle of sale &gt; review &gt; sale.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><b>Pro tip:</b> if you use WooCommerce to sell your products, you can integrate this function thanks to the <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-review-for-discounts/\">WooCommerce Review for Discount</a> plugin.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In this case it might also help to integrate an automatic email system to remind customers to leave reviews in exchange for a discount, in order to inform them about this offer and get back to old customers.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This function can be integrated to WooCommerce as well thanks to the dedicated <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-review-reminder/\">WooCommerce Review Reminder</a> plugin.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Increase the value of each single customer</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Once you have found new customers and convinced them to buy, why not increase the amount of money they’d spend?</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">We usually believe that discounts decrease the average values of cutomers since, in fact, they will spend less then if they’d buy at full price. Truth is this apparent weakness might be the starting point to increase the average transaction value for each customer.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">How?</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Think about the usual 3&#215;2 offer and its persuasive power: if you buy at least two products, the third one is free. This typo of offer uses discounts specifically to increase the average value of each customer.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Let’s consider a standard scenario:<em> I have an e-commerce store with 100 average monthly customers spending 50$ each. This makes for a monthly income of 5000$</em></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Now I will propose a discount based on the cart value: you will obtain a 20% off discount if your cart is worth at least 120$.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Many customers will be tempted to purchase several products although they might not need them immediately, in order to use the discount offered.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Doing this, thanks to discounts I increased the average transaction value per customer from 50$ to 60$ or 70$ or 80$ (according to the number of people who accept to use the discount by spending more), which will increase the gross income of my e-commerce store.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">If you use WooCommerce, you can create a discount system based on the cart value, number of products or more using the <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-dynamic-pricing-and-discounts/\">WooCommerce Dynamic Pricing and Discounts</a> plugin.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Get back to the customers who left your store</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">On 100 customers who enter your website, 80 of them leave it in a few seconds. Of those 20 left, almost 90% of them won’t complete the purchase process, leaving the cart to before completing the purchase.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>This sure is a sad scenario, but it also represents a high potential: if your customers are only those 2 who get past these obstacles, then if you could only save 10% of those who left their cart behind, you will have doubled your sales!</em></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">But how can you do this? Usually the most effective way is to create an automated system that allows you to send an email to those customers who left their cart, trying to persuade them to complete the pending sale (after all if they had items in their cart, then they must have been interested in those products, so it shouldn’t be hard to reignite their interest)</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And here we can see <strong>discounts becoming once again the right tool for our purpose</strong>: in the reminder email include the discount voucher and watch customers come back to your store. Most of those who abandon their cart do so because they found themselves facing unexpected expenses such as shipping fees, so offering them a solution that makes them save money can be a very persuasive technique.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">As usual, if you use <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/woocommerce/\" rel=\"nofollow\">WooCommerce</a>, there’s a plugin that allows you to create this system automatically: <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-recover-abandoned-cart/\">WooCommerce Recover Abandoned Cart</a>.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And you are set! As you could see, in the right hands the same tool can be used in different circumstances with varying results: it’s all down to you and your creativity!</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:83:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/increase-sales-thanks-to-discounts-part-2/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"Increase sales thanks to discounts: how to use them and which ones you should choose (1/2)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:78:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/increase-sales-thanks-to-discounts-part-1/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/increase-sales-thanks-to-discounts-part-1/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 25 May 2016 08:24:42 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"https://yithemes.com/?p=791600\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:314:\"I tried putting myself in the shoes of a seller who is trying to find new ways to improve their online sales. The articles you can find online generally show two aspects of the same tool: why you should use and why you shouldn&#8217;t. Consider discounts: one of the most commonly used marketing tools in [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Andrea Presenti\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8943:\"<p dir=\"ltr\">I tried putting myself in the shoes of a seller who is trying to find new ways to improve their online sales. The articles you can find online generally show two aspects of the same tool: why you should use and why you shouldn&#8217;t.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Consider discounts: one of the most commonly used marketing tools in the world, anybody who has a store (physical or online) sooner or later find themselves introducing discounts as an attempt to increase sales.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">If I looked for information about how to add a discount system in my e-commerce store online, I would then find two kind of articles:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Some about the reasons why I shouldn&#8217;t do it: since they lower your gain rate and they reduce sales once they are no longer active.</li>\r\n 	<li>Some about the reasons why I should: they increase sales, the average purchase and improve customers satisfaction.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">What should matter to the users isn&#8217;t why they should or shouldn&#8217;t do it though, but HOW to use this tool: good or bad consequences are a direct result of how this system was used.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>So this is why I decided to write two articles that would explain how discounts work as a marketing tool, their different uses and the results they might bring.</em></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In this first article we are going to check out the potential of a time limited discount and the importance of discounts an element of elaborate schemes such as loyalty programs.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Timed discounts – The Principle of Scarcity</h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">I&#8217;m sure you already noticed how many discounts have a time limit before they expire, why is that?</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Many people simply <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/how-to-increase-the-conversion-rate-on-your-timed-offers-list-for-registered-users-only-on-your-online-store/\">create a timed promotion</a> because they know it works, since everybody else does them, so they might as well try!</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Understanding the mechanics behind the success of a marketing tool though, is essential to be able to use it at its full potential.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">A timed discounts owes its effectiveness to a subconscious psychological process named “Principle of Scarcity” by Robert Cialdini, one of the top expert worldwide when it comes to neuro-marketing.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Cialdini&#8217;s principles focus on those automatic connections our brain makes due to the social environment we live in (or even those who are naturally ingrained in our minds) and timed promotions are a clear case of these.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">When you add an expiration date to a discount, you stress out the fact that it won&#8217;t be possible to use that discount after a given date. This seems obvious, but this is where it gets interesting: the point here isn&#8217;t the discount itself or its expiration date.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Once an offer is over we cannot obtain a specific item at a discounted special price ever again and for our subconscious that&#8217;s just unbearable. Here&#8217;s a simple example: Give a child ten toys then forbid him to play with one of them.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Most of the times, the child is going to pick that specific toy to play with, since the subconscious part of our brain refuses any limitation to our freedom.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Many things change while growing up, but not the subconscious processes that guide our actions, that&#8217;s why when we offer a timed discount, our brains understands it as: “If you don&#8217;t buy this right now, you will NEVER be able to do so EVER again!”</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Not only that: a timed promotion triggers yet another subconscious process, meaning our desire to find “shortcuts”. We spend our life longing to own items that are out of our league and we are often explained that in order to obtain something valuable, we need to pay (with work or money). This is why a discount is perceived as a shortcut that allows us to get our desired items without having to pay for their full value.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This is all very interesting, but why is it so important to know these things? Well, since now you know which aspects you should focus on in order to increase the effectiveness of your promotion!</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">I&#8217;ve seen many people trying to improve the effectiveness of their timed discounts by increasing the discount rate, repeating the same offer over and over, etc.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And all they gained from this was:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>They lowered their own profit rate</li>\r\n 	<li>They lowered the effectiveness of the tool itself, since customers KNOW they are not dealing with a unique occasion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">It might also be relevant to stress out just how much customers would miss if they were to pass on said offer, how unique it is and how much more valuable the item is compared to its discounted price.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The best way to prove that these tools are effective comes form the fact that they are used by massive companies such as Amazon: the worldwide number one leader in sales has a dedicated section for flash sales including a countdown on each single product.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Timed-deals.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-791605\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Timed-deals.jpg\" alt=\"Timed-deals\" width=\"805\" height=\"403\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Timed-deals.jpg 805w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Timed-deals-300x150.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Timed-deals-768x384.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Timed-deals-88x45.jpg 88w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Timed-deals-382x191.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/Timed-deals-270x135.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 805px) 100vw, 805px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Offering discount is always risky for sellers, but when you know the right way to offer it, it becomes a very limited risk.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><b>Pro-tip</b>: If you use WooCommerce, you can introduce timed discounts for your products (just like Amazon does) including countdowns by using the<a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-product-countdown/\"> WooCommerce Product Countdown</a> plugin.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>A discount as reward for your work</h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Another very common way used to offer discounts is to <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/woocommerce-how-to-encourage-sales-thanks-to-loyalty-points/\">create a Loyalty Program</a>: I&#8217;m sure you&#8217;ve seen many store of all kinds offer the opportunity to gain points and exchange them for discounts or rewards.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Why do so many stores use this marketing system? Because it clearly works and because many others use it.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>But how does a Loyalty Program work exactly? And how is that different from a single discount?</em></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">First of all its effectiveness: discounts often increase the possibility of purchases from customers, often risking to stop our relationship with the customer if we don&#8217;t manage to keep their attention on our store after the first transaction. A Loyalty Program works differently: other than being an excellent marketing tool (maybe including rewards other than just discounts, no matter if it takes many points to get them) the program enhances the value of each single purchase.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Why?</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Do you remember when I said that we were taught that a valuable object has to be paid with work or money? That&#8217;s the frame of mind we were taught and it has two direct consequences: an expensive object suddenly acquires value and we are not particularly keen on spending our money.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This last points is why it&#8217;s hard to convince customers to buy something, and I&#8217;m sure it happened to you as well to wonder: “Did I make the right choice spending money for this item?”</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Thanks to Loyalty Programs you can stay away from this risk, since your sales will no longer be an end in themselves but will become a step in a path that leads to a reward. And this feeling grows stronger the more purchases your customers make.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">So this is how a simple discount may become a part of a much more complex marketing plan.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><b>Pro-tip: </b>If you use WooComerce for your store, you can start your own Loyalty Program using the<a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-points-and-rewards/\"> WooCommerce Points and Rewards</a> plugin,</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In the next article we are going to see more uses of discounts as a marketing tool, specifically, we are going to see how to use them to increase sales and the average income per customer.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:83:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/increase-sales-thanks-to-discounts-part-1/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:87:\"Increase sales on digital products making the checkout process on WooCommerce immediate\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:124:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/increase-sales-on-digital-products-making-the-checkout-process-on-woocommerce-immediate/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:133:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/increase-sales-on-digital-products-making-the-checkout-process-on-woocommerce-immediate/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 16 May 2016 13:29:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"https://yithemes.com/?p=791089\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:343:\"Have you ever wondered which is the most important moment during the purchase process? According to the statistics based on the most searched words on Google it would seem like it&#8217;s the first step: bringing customers to your store. If this is a key aspect, since no business can exist without customers, focusing exclusively on [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Andrea Presenti\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:8429:\"<p dir=\"ltr\">Have you ever wondered which is the most important moment during the purchase process?</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">According to the statistics based on the most searched words on Google it would seem like it&#8217;s the first step: bringing customers to your store.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">If this is a key aspect, since no business can exist without customers, focusing exclusively on the first step may distract us from the following steps and render all of our work futile.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">It&#8217;s pointless to invest time and money, bring thousands of people to our website if only a few of these will effectively purchase something.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In these cases, <strong>we need to make every single aspect of our store efficent</strong>, in order to make customers curious and encourage them to make purchases, and this is when problems start to arise.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Many of those who seek a solution for their low sales ofen underestimate the last step of purchases:<a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/woocommerce-one-click-checkout-increase-the-conversion-rate-by-speding-up-the-checkout-process/\"> the checkout process</a>.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Think about it: while it&#8217;s natural to consider that once customers have added their product to the cart, then they are going to purchase it and that&#8217;s it, right? <b>Truth is that almost 90% of the people who begin going through a checkout process are not going to bring it to a conclusion&#8230;</b> That is a staggering amount!</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/One-click-checkout-percentage.jpg\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-791096\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/One-click-checkout-percentage.jpg\" alt=\"One-click-checkout-percentage\" width=\"983\" height=\"329\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/One-click-checkout-percentage.jpg 983w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/One-click-checkout-percentage-300x100.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/One-click-checkout-percentage-768x257.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/One-click-checkout-percentage-382x128.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/One-click-checkout-percentage-270x90.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 983px) 100vw, 983px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">I&#8217;ve written articles about this before, focusing on <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/how-to-facilitate-the-checkout-process-in-a-few-simple-steps/\">how it&#8217;s possible to improve the various aspects of the checkout</a> process in order to sensibly lower this rate, however today I would like to focus specifically on <b>digital products sales</b>.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">One of the things I use to say in my articles is that a tool is only as effective as the hand that wields it. Which has proven effective countless times.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Specifically, a tool needs to be used in different ways according to different situations: and one of the most common mistakes is to consider a real life item purchase process to be similar to a digital product purchase process.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Data and cart abandonment rate at hand prove us wrong: a tool that&#8217;s designed for a specific purpose is a hundred times more effective than a generic one.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Let&#8217;s take two pretty common case and compare them:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Jack has an online clothing store. He manages to work both for end users and sellers and sells clothes for any age or gender.</li>\r\n 	<li>Marcus has an online store for digital products: fiction and nonfiction     e-books.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Both stores have a huge customer pool (since everybody needs clothes and thankfully people still read books) but the way in which both stores need to handle customers, especially in the final steps of their sales, is completely different.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Let&#8217;s consider Jack&#8217;s store: clearly when Jack sells a pair of trousers, there&#8217;s a certain amount of information he needs to know before sending the product to his customer: such as name, family name, shipping address, city, postcode, state, etc&#8230;</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And despite the average customer is particularly wary about entering personal data in a website, they comply since they are aware that that&#8217;s a required step in order to receive what they bought, customers don&#8217;t ask question as for why they are being asked for a billing address or the size of the trousers they are buying, they are clearly required information.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Now let&#8217;s think about the customers that are going to purchase e-books from Marcus&#8217; store.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>The first substantial difference between the two checkout processes is <strong>THE WAIT</strong>.</em></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">We often forget about the huge differences between real life purchases and online ones, just consider the time in between the payment and the moment in which you actually receive the product.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In a real life store your product is available right away, you often hold it in your hand even before payment, while online sales require the customer to wait through the whole shipping process, and while they accept this wait, they can&#8217;t avoid being concerned about it until it&#8217;s delivered. Think about how many customers constantly check the tracking code for their products!</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With digital products we don&#8217;t need to accept or worry about anything, people will pay and receive what they paid for right away.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">It&#8217;s clear now that we are dealing with two different kind of customers: Jack&#8217;s customers have accepted to wait days in order to receive the product they paid for, while Marcus&#8217; customers require a quicker service and in case the checkout process was to take an extra minute or so, that would have a much worse impact on them rather then the first kind of customers.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>The second difference lies in <strong>INFORMATION</strong></em>, As I&#8217;ve said before, if I know an item needs to be shipped I&#8217;m not surprised to enter personal information about who I am and where I live, but what if I need to buy an e-book? Wouldn&#8217;t that be natural to wonder “Why the hell would I need to tell you where I live?”</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">I often see online stores for digital products leaving their checkout process in the default WooCommerce settings, which implies asking customers they address, state, zip code etc.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The checkout system will work as intended, but it surely is an imperfect tool and as such it might affect our transactions.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Aiming for immediacy is essential not only for digital products but also for any other item that&#8217;s meant to be sold. The attention span and inclination towards purchases customers have are limited, so if we manage to quicken the purchase process, sales will increase right away.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This is why you need to ask for selected specific information according to the kind of item you intend to sell.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Some may object that certain information, however useless they might seem from a customer&#8217;s perspective, are required for tax purposes or in order to process bills, in which case, rather then avoid asking for them, why not just postpone them? Purchases need to be immediate; email, password and then payment, that&#8217;s it.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">You need more information? Well, you can ask them during the download, making it available only for those who completed their profile, doing this will prevent you from losing customers and you can ask for all the information you require, maybe even explaining why you need to do so.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And for those using WooCommerce but don&#8217;t have the chance to customize their checkout process since they don&#8217;t have the required skills and would rather ask a developer, I recommend the<a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-quick-checkout-for-digital-goods/\"> WooCommerce Quick Checkout for Digital Goods</a> plugin which allows you to edit the checkout fields and postpone those that are not immediately required.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">If your average customer leaves the checkout 40 seconds into it, then all you need to do is make it last 39 seconds.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:129:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/increase-sales-on-digital-products-making-the-checkout-process-on-woocommerce-immediate/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"How Copywriters can sell online writing services in a few steps\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:100:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/how-copywriters-can-sell-online-writing-services-in-a-few-steps/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:109:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/how-copywriters-can-sell-online-writing-services-in-a-few-steps/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 10 May 2016 10:33:03 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"https://yithemes.com/?p=790662\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:313:\"One of the most common web search is “How to gain money working online” and, sadly, most of the results to this query are all but trustworthy However, there are indeed online jobs available, for instance there are many chances for those who like to write and want to test their skills in this field. [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Andrea Presenti\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:35702:\"<p dir=\"ltr\">One of the most common web search is “How to gain money working online” and, sadly, most of the results to this query are all but trustworthy</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">However, there are indeed online jobs available, for instance <em>there are many chances for those who like to write and want to test their skills in this field</em>.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The first field that comes to mind is the one concerning writing blog articles, which are generally paid a given amount of money for each article or for each word.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Ghost-writers are also another possibility offered by this field: writers that offer to write books, speeches, tales and so on, under somebody else&#8217;s name.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">So here is the question: “How can I sell this kind of service?”</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Many authors use preexisting websites such as <a href=\"https://www.textbroker.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Textbroker</a>, which operates in this field since 2008.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>So how do these writers “market places” work?</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Customers ask for an article and decide the minimum amount of word, text quality and style (informal, journalistic, review, etc). Now the article can be booked by an author that will receive a share of the total amount the user has set.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">So why chose a service like this? There is one main reason, the same reason why any vendor would chose a market place to sell: the great amount of customers and possibilities offered by a website like that.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">But this kind of online market also has its down size: a big demand also means a lot of supply and competition, other then the fact that profits are often limited by the share authors receive.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">That&#8217;s why it would be a good idea to try and offer an independent service, creating an e-commerce and offering articles just like any other products on sale.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">So how would you sell such a service? One in which customers get to decide their own parameters and pay according to them?</p>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"client_body\">\r\n<div id=\"col_messages\">\r\n<div class=\"row-fluid\">\r\n<div id=\"messages_container\" class=\"\">\r\n<div id=\"monkey_scroll_wrapper_for_msgs_scroller_div\" class=\"monkey_scroll_wrapper \">\r\n<div class=\"monkey_scroll_hider  scrolling\">\r\n<div id=\"msgs_scroller_div\" class=\"monkey_scroller\">\r\n<div id=\"msgs_div\" class=\"msgs_holder\">\r\n<div class=\"day_container\">\r\n<div class=\"day_msgs\">\r\n<div class=\"message_content \"><span class=\"message_body\">This is what we are going to find out, thanks to a simple WooCommerce plugin.</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<h1>Required Plugin</h1>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-product-add-ons/\" target=\"_blank\">YITH WooCommerce Product add ons</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h1>Plugin Configuration</h1>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">A common product page cannot offer a service like the one we intend to offer, since we need prices that vary according to the needs expressed by our customers.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In order to offer a variable service then, you need to use a plugin that allows you to enter additional fields and set a price for each one of them.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In this tutorial I’m going to create a “<strong>Ghostwriting Service</strong>” product that will allow customers to chose between these features:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Article length</li>\r\n 	<li>Writing Style</li>\r\n 	<li>Review by another copywriter</li>\r\n 	<li>Delivery Date</li>\r\n 	<li>Articles Images</li>\r\n 	<li>Blog Entry Service</li>\r\n 	<li>Email of the recipient</li>\r\n 	<li>Layout</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">As you can see there are many options, but in this case it&#8217;s always best to offer a product with as many customization options as possible, so that each customer gets to buy exactly what they are after.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Let&#8217;s see how to create these variations step by step.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The first thing you should do is to create the “<em>Ghoswriting Service</em>” product, just like you would with any other product:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790669\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790669\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing\" width=\"939\" height=\"533\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing.jpg 939w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-300x170.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-768x436.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-382x217.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-241x137.jpg 241w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 939px) 100vw, 939px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Once it&#8217;s created, this is what it&#8217;s going to look like in our store:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-view.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790692\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790692\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-view.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-view\" width=\"900\" height=\"575\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-view.jpg 900w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-view-300x192.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-view-768x491.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-view-382x244.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-view-214x137.jpg 214w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Now that you have your product, you should add all of the fields required to make it a customizable service for your cusomers.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Once the plugin is installed and activated, go to <b>YITH Plugin &gt; YITH WooCommerce Advanced Product Options </b>and you will find two screens containing the general options of this plugin: <b>General</b> and <b>Variations</b>:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/customize-label-button-ghostwriting.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790668\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790668\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/customize-label-button-ghostwriting.jpg\" alt=\"customize-label-button-ghostwriting\" width=\"774\" height=\"428\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/customize-label-button-ghostwriting.jpg 774w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/customize-label-button-ghostwriting-300x166.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/customize-label-button-ghostwriting-768x425.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/customize-label-button-ghostwriting-382x211.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/customize-label-button-ghostwriting-248x137.jpg 248w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 774px) 100vw, 774px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Among the many options you will find:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The position of each added option, whether you want to place them before or after the “Add to Cart” button.</li>\r\n 	<li>In the “Add to cart button label” field you can insert a custom     text that will identify the customizable products in your store:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/button-label-ghostwriter.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790664\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790664\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/button-label-ghostwriter.jpg\" alt=\"button-label-ghostwriter\" width=\"434\" height=\"362\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/button-label-ghostwriter.jpg 434w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/button-label-ghostwriter-300x250.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/button-label-ghostwriter-382x319.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/button-label-ghostwriter-164x137.jpg 164w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 434px) 100vw, 434px\" /></a>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Choose what to display, between images, title and description, to show the possible variation in the product page.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Once these options are configured the way you like, you can move to the second tab: “Variations”:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-backend-variations.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-785748\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-785748\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-backend-variations-1024x597.jpg\" alt=\"customize-product-page-backend-variations\" width=\"1024\" height=\"597\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-backend-variations-1024x597.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-backend-variations-300x175.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-backend-variations-768x448.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-backend-variations-382x223.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-backend-variations-235x137.jpg 235w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-backend-variations-303x178.jpg 303w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-backend-variations.jpg 1134w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In this section you will find more settings, suche as how the tooltip of each feature will look like in the product page.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Now you can move on to the extra field you wish to add in the product page, so go to <b>Products &gt; YITH WooCommerce Product Add-ons &gt; Add Group</b>:<a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-1.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-786453\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-786453\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-1.jpg\" alt=\"customize-product-page-group\" width=\"801\" height=\"390\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-1.jpg 801w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-1-300x146.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-1-768x374.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-1-382x186.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-1-270x131.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 801px) 100vw, 801px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The first thing you need to do is decide which name you wish to assign to the group of customization rules you are creating. Since the subject is writing itself, you could call it “<strong>Writing</strong>”.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-add-group.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790670\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790670\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-add-group.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-add-group\" width=\"829\" height=\"574\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-add-group.jpg 829w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-add-group-300x208.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-add-group-768x532.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-add-group-382x264.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-add-group-198x137.jpg 198w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 829px) 100vw, 829px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Once you picked the name, you should link it to the product (or product category) you wish to apply these variations to. So now enter the product you previously created:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-add-group-product.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790671\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790671\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-add-group-product.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-add-group-product\" width=\"765\" height=\"546\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-add-group-product.jpg 765w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-add-group-product-300x214.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-add-group-product-382x273.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-add-group-product-192x137.jpg 192w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 765px) 100vw, 765px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Now you should create all the variations you wish to offer in your service, by clicking on <b>Add new</b>, which you can find at the bottom of the page you just created.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghostwriting-add-new-group.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790672\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790672\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghostwriting-add-new-group.jpg\" alt=\"ghostwriting-add-new-group\" width=\"695\" height=\"415\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghostwriting-add-new-group.jpg 695w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghostwriting-add-new-group-300x179.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghostwriting-add-new-group-382x228.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghostwriting-add-new-group-229x137.jpg 229w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 695px) 100vw, 695px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">You can create all kinds of variations, as you can see in the drop down menu:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-all.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-785750\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-785750\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-all-1024x535.jpg\" alt=\"customize-product-page-group-all\" width=\"1024\" height=\"535\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-all-1024x535.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-all-300x157.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-all-768x401.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-all-88x45.jpg 88w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-all-382x199.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-all-262x137.jpg 262w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-all.jpg 1318w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">So now you are going to create the options you wish to display in the product page, one by one.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Article Length</h1>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">One of the most important fields is the one that offers the chance to choose the length of the article a customer wishes to purchase. So create a “select” field and set up the choices you wish to offer, setting up a price for each variation.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remember to enter the text that&#8217;s going to describe your option in the “Option Label” field:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-length.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790684\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790684\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-length.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-length\" width=\"953\" height=\"514\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-length.jpg 953w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-length-300x162.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-length-768x414.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-length-382x206.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-length-254x137.jpg 254w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 953px) 100vw, 953px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And this is what it&#8217;s going to look like in the product page, once it&#8217;s saved:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-length-front.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790685\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790685\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-length-front.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-length-front\" width=\"919\" height=\"494\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-length-front.jpg 919w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-length-front-300x161.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-length-front-768x413.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-length-front-382x205.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-length-front-255x137.jpg 255w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 919px) 100vw, 919px\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Writing Style</h1>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Different articles require different writing styles, that&#8217;s why you need to pick a “select” field again and set up the Writing Style (without assigning a cost to it this time).</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remember to enter the text that&#8217;s going to describe your option in the “Option Label” field:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-style.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790689\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790689\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-style.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-style\" width=\"921\" height=\"436\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-style.jpg 921w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-style-300x142.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-style-768x364.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-style-382x181.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-style-270x128.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 921px) 100vw, 921px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And that&#8217;s how this option is going to look like in your product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-style-front.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790690\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790690\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-style-front.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-style-front\" width=\"923\" height=\"426\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-style-front.jpg 923w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-style-front-300x138.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-style-front-768x354.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-style-front-382x176.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-style-front-270x125.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 923px) 100vw, 923px\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Review by another copywriter</h1>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>Offering a further text review is a guarantee for quality</em>, so create a “checkbox” field where your customers can buy this extra service.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remember to enter the text that&#8217;s going to describe this option in the “Option Label” field:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-review.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790676\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790676\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-review.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-copy-review\" width=\"925\" height=\"365\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-review.jpg 925w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-review-300x118.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-review-768x303.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-review-382x151.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-review-270x107.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 925px) 100vw, 925px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And that&#8217;show this variation will be displayed in the product field:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-review-front.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790677\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790677\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-review-front.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-copy-review-front\" width=\"944\" height=\"406\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-review-front.jpg 944w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-review-front-300x129.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-review-front-768x330.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-review-front-382x164.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-review-front-270x116.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 944px) 100vw, 944px\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Delivery date</h1>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Now create an option customers can choose the day by which the articles need to be written. To do so, create a “Date” field.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remember to enter the text that&#8217;s going to describe your option in the “Option Label” field:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-eta.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790680\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790680\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-eta.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-eta\" width=\"920\" height=\"353\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-eta.jpg 920w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-eta-300x115.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-eta-768x295.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-eta-382x147.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-eta-270x104.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 920px) 100vw, 920px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This is how this variation is going to be displayed in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-eta-front.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790681\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790681\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-eta-front.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-eta-front\" width=\"916\" height=\"597\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-eta-front.jpg 916w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-eta-front-300x196.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-eta-front-768x501.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-eta-front-382x249.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-eta-front-210x137.jpg 210w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 916px) 100vw, 916px\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Article Images</h1>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Articles often require images in them. For this, create an “Upload” field which will offer the chance to upload images directly into the product page.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remember to enter the text that describes this option in the “Option Label” field:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-upload.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790678\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790678\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-upload.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-copy-upload\" width=\"763\" height=\"393\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-upload.jpg 763w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-upload-300x155.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-upload-88x45.jpg 88w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-upload-382x197.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-upload-266x137.jpg 266w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 763px) 100vw, 763px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And this is how this variation is going to be displayed in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-upload-front.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790679\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790679\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-upload-front.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-copy-upload-front\" width=\"764\" height=\"419\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-upload-front.jpg 764w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-upload-front-300x165.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-upload-front-382x210.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-copy-upload-front-250x137.jpg 250w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 764px) 100vw, 764px\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Email address of the recipient</h1>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Clearly this is necessary to be able to send the article to your customer once it&#8217;s completed. To do so create a “textarea” field your customers will use to enter their email address.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remember to enter the text that describes this option in the “Option Label” field:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-login-email.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790687\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790687\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-login-email.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-login-email\" width=\"792\" height=\"404\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-login-email.jpg 792w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-login-email-300x153.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-login-email-768x392.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-login-email-88x45.jpg 88w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-login-email-382x195.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-login-email-270x137.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 792px) 100vw, 792px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And this is how this option is going to look like in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-login-email-front.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790688\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790688\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-login-email-front.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-login-email-front\" width=\"729\" height=\"326\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-login-email-front.jpg 729w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-login-email-front-300x134.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-login-email-front-382x171.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-login-email-front-270x121.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 729px) 100vw, 729px\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Blog entry service</h1>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Many customers may appreciate an options that allows them to upload an article directly into their blogs. <em>To do so, create a “checkbox” that will identify this variation and add its specific price</em>.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remember to enter the text that describes this option in the “Option Label” field:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-blog-entry.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790673\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790673\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-blog-entry.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-blog-entry\" width=\"885\" height=\"402\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-blog-entry.jpg 885w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-blog-entry-300x136.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-blog-entry-768x349.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-blog-entry-382x174.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-blog-entry-270x123.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 885px) 100vw, 885px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And this is what it&#8217;s going to look like in the product field:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-blog-entry-front.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790674\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790674\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-blog-entry-front.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-blog-entry-front\" width=\"614\" height=\"192\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-blog-entry-front.jpg 614w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-blog-entry-front-300x94.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-blog-entry-front-382x119.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-blog-entry-front-270x84.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 614px) 100vw, 614px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In order to insert an article directly into a blog you are going to need its access data and the blog&#8217;s url. Create a “textarea” field that&#8217;s only going to be displayed once customers click on the “blog entry” checkbox.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remember to enter the text that describes your option in the “Option Label” field:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-login-data.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790686\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790686\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-login-data.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-login-data\" width=\"828\" height=\"467\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-login-data.jpg 828w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-login-data-300x169.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-login-data-768x433.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-login-data-382x215.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-login-data-243x137.jpg 243w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 828px) 100vw, 828px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">As you can see, in order to display this option only when another one is selected, you need to enter that variation in the “Requirement” field.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And this is what it&#8217;s going to look like in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-blog-entry-front-data.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790675\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790675\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-blog-entry-front-data.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-blog-entry-front-data\" width=\"716\" height=\"518\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-blog-entry-front-data.jpg 716w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-blog-entry-front-data-300x217.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-blog-entry-front-data-382x276.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-blog-entry-front-data-189x137.jpg 189w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 716px) 100vw, 716px\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Layout</h1>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">A layout service, better if saved as PDF,<strong> might be one of the most required services for a text</strong>. Create a “checkbox” option to offer this service.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remember to enter the text that describes your option in the “Option Label” field:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-layout.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790682\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790682\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-layout.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-layout\" width=\"809\" height=\"436\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-layout.jpg 809w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-layout-300x162.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-layout-768x414.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-layout-382x206.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-layout-254x137.jpg 254w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 809px) 100vw, 809px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And this is what this option is going to look like in the product page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-layout-front.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790683\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790683\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-layout-front.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-layout-front\" width=\"651\" height=\"416\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-layout-front.jpg 651w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-layout-front-300x192.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-layout-front-382x244.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-layout-front-214x137.jpg 214w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 651px) 100vw, 651px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Now that you have created all of the required options, this is what your product is going to look like:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-view-after.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790693\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790693\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-view-after.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-view-after\" width=\"910\" height=\"729\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-view-after.jpg 910w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-view-after-300x240.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-view-after-768x615.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-view-after-382x306.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-view-after-171x137.jpg 171w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 910px) 100vw, 910px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And once they have chosen all of the services they need, customers will be displayed the final price, divided between base price and extra services:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-total.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-790691\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-790691\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-total.jpg\" alt=\"ghost-writing-total\" width=\"651\" height=\"416\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-total.jpg 651w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-total-300x192.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-total-382x244.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/05/ghost-writing-total-214x137.jpg 214w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 651px) 100vw, 651px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Start to sell your custom texts right now!</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:105:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/how-copywriters-can-sell-online-writing-services-in-a-few-steps/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:89:\"WooCommerce: Selling flowers with home delivery service and dedications (like Interflora)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:123:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/woocommerce-selling-flowers-with-home-delivery-service-and-dedications-like-interflora/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:132:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/woocommerce-selling-flowers-with-home-delivery-service-and-dedications-like-interflora/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 02 May 2016 10:41:52 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"https://yithemes.com/?p=787136\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:333:\"The flower language is so old and ingrained in our culture that even today, despite technology made interpersonal relationships colder, there is no better gift than a flower arrangement. And I&#8217;m not just talking about women, that usually are the target of this kind of gift: a bouquet is a welcome gift in many cases: [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Andrea Presenti\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30370:\"<p dir=\"ltr\">The flower language is so old and ingrained in our culture that even today, despite technology made interpersonal relationships colder, there is no better gift than a flower arrangement.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And I&#8217;m not just talking about women, that usually are the target of this kind of gift: a bouquet is a welcome gift in many cases: a graduation, a degree, a birthday, a promotion, a birth and so on.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">I&#8217;m not going through the potential displayed by a store that appeals to such a big customer pool, I&#8217;d rather use this article to explain to you how to properly exploit this potential.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Clearly, despite the fact that it&#8217;s nice to receive flowers from people we love, it&#8217;s not always possible to visit a florist shop, buy a flower arrangement and then personally deliver it to our loved ones.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">We tend to travel and get further from them, that&#8217;s why services like Interflora are born.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The <strong>interflora service</strong> is internationally known: just go to their website, choose the kind of floral composition you are interested in, the date of delivery and content of the card and they will handle the rest.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Interflora was so successful that their service is offered in over 100 countries worldwide, which may lead us to thing that the way this service works is complicated and hard to carry out.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">But as you can see in this article, things often seem harder then they actually are.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Required Plugins:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-product-add-ons/\">YITH WooCommerce Product add-ons</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Plugins Configuration</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">So, what&#8217;s Interflora&#8217;s strength? It&#8217;s the chance to add a custom message to your bouquet, turning a generic and cold gift into something heartwarming and personal.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">It&#8217;s also important to be able to specify when and where to deliver it, to avoid losing it or late deliveries (which is very bad for gifts).</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Rather then setting a fixed price or a quote system (which needs exchanging emails and it&#8217;s a time consuming process for both you and your customers), you are going to insert these variations straight into the product itself.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">As always a direct example is the best way to understand how it works, that&#8217;s why I&#8217;m going to create a “bouquet of roses” item that will include the following customization options:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Varying bouquet size</li>\r\n	<li>Destination</li>\r\n	<li>Delivery date</li>\r\n	<li>Preferred time of delivery (morning, afternoon, evening)</li>\r\n	<li>A card including</li>\r\n	<li>Special instructions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">So let&#8217;s create the “Roses bouquet” product, as you would with any other product:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-view-flower.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-787153\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-787153\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-view-flower.jpg\" alt=\"customize-product-page-view-flower\" width=\"905\" height=\"532\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-view-flower.jpg 905w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-view-flower-300x176.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-view-flower-768x451.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-view-flower-382x225.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-view-flower-233x137.jpg 233w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-view-flower-400x235.jpg 400w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-view-flower-303x178.jpg 303w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 905px) 100vw, 905px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Now you should add the required fields for the customization of your product.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Once the plugin is installed and activated, go to <b>YITH Plugin &gt; YITH WooCommerce Product add-ons </b>and you will find the plugin general settings:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-label-button.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-787140\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-787140\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-label-button.jpg\" alt=\"customize-label-button\" width=\"774\" height=\"428\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-label-button.jpg 774w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-label-button-300x166.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-label-button-768x425.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-label-button-382x211.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-label-button-248x137.jpg 248w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 774px) 100vw, 774px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In here you can set the general configuration of the plugin, specifically, you can choose:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Where to display the extra options, whether if before or after the “Add to Cart” button. In this tutorial they are going to be displayed afterwards, so I&#8217;m going to chose “After “<b>add to cart</b>“ button”.</li>\r\n	<li>You can also customize the text of the “add to cart” button in the catalog, to indicate which products are customizable: by entering, for instance, “<b>customize your bouquet</b>”, the product in the shop page is going to look like this:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-your-bouquet.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-787155\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-787155\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-your-bouquet.jpg\" alt=\"customize-your-bouquet\" width=\"606\" height=\"452\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-your-bouquet.jpg 606w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-your-bouquet-300x224.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-your-bouquet-382x285.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-your-bouquet-184x137.jpg 184w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 606px) 100vw, 606px\" /></a>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Choose what to display in the customization options: title, images and description.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Once these options are configured the way you want, you can move to the second tab, “Variations”:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-backend-variations.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-785748\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-785748\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-backend-variations-1024x597.jpg\" alt=\"customize-product-page-backend-variations\" width=\"1024\" height=\"597\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-backend-variations-1024x597.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-backend-variations-300x175.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-backend-variations-768x448.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-backend-variations-382x223.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-backend-variations-235x137.jpg 235w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-backend-variations-303x178.jpg 303w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-backend-variations.jpg 1134w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In here you will find the other settings, including how the tooltip for each feature is going to look in the product page.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In order to create additional fields your customers can use to customize their order, you need to go to <b>Products &gt; YITH WooCommerce Product add-ons &gt; Add Group</b>:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-1.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-786453\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-786453\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-1.jpg\" alt=\"customize-product-page-group\" width=\"801\" height=\"390\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-1.jpg 801w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-1-300x146.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-1-768x374.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-1-382x186.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-1-270x131.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 801px) 100vw, 801px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In this tutorial I&#8217;ve called this group “Flowers”, but you can obviously name it however you like.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/flowers-group.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-787156\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-787156\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/flowers-group.jpg\" alt=\"flowers-group\" width=\"737\" height=\"190\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/flowers-group.jpg 737w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/flowers-group-300x77.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/flowers-group-382x98.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/flowers-group-270x70.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 737px) 100vw, 737px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">You can also add extra fields to single products or whole categories.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In case you want to offer the same service on all the plants in your website, you can do it by entering all of your products into the same category and then assign a customization option to it.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In this tutorial I entered all the products in the “Bouquet” category:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Bouquet-category.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-787138\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-787138\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Bouquet-category.jpg\" alt=\"Bouquet-category\" width=\"735\" height=\"483\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Bouquet-category.jpg 735w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Bouquet-category-300x197.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Bouquet-category-382x251.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Bouquet-category-208x137.jpg 208w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 735px) 100vw, 735px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">After picking the category, select it in the group you are going to create:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-products-flowers.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-787142\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-787142\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-products-flowers.jpg\" alt=\"customize-product-page-group-products-flowers\" width=\"608\" height=\"409\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-products-flowers.jpg 608w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-products-flowers-300x202.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-products-flowers-382x257.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-products-flowers-204x137.jpg 204w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Now you need to enter the customization option you established earlier, by clicking on <b>Add new</b>:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-787143\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-787143\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers.jpg\" alt=\"customize-product-page-group-types-flowers\" width=\"608\" height=\"409\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers.jpg 608w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-300x202.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-382x257.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-204x137.jpg 204w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 608px) 100vw, 608px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Using the drop down menu you&#8217;ll see a list of the type of fields you can create:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-all.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-787144\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-787144\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-all.jpg\" alt=\"customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-all\" width=\"889\" height=\"331\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-all.jpg 889w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-all-300x112.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-all-768x286.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-all-382x142.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-all-270x101.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 889px) 100vw, 889px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Now you need to decide how to display your customization options. In this tutorial I want to set the three bouquet size options as always visible and hide the other options under a checkbox users need to check to see.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Bouquet Size</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">To set up the choice among different sizes, create a “labels” field and enter the options and their related prices in it:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Select-size.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-787159\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-787159\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Select-size-1024x385.jpg\" alt=\"Select-size\" width=\"1024\" height=\"385\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Select-size-1024x385.jpg 1024w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Select-size-300x113.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Select-size-768x289.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Select-size-382x144.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Select-size-270x102.jpg 270w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Select-size.jpg 1270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Add a checkbox and assign a specific name to it (in my case it&#8217;s Customize your gift):</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/checkbox-customize.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-787139\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-787139\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/checkbox-customize.jpg\" alt=\"checkbox-customize\" width=\"826\" height=\"328\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/checkbox-customize.jpg 826w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/checkbox-customize-300x119.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/checkbox-customize-768x305.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/checkbox-customize-382x152.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/checkbox-customize-270x107.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 826px) 100vw, 826px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Now you can enter the other variations, carefully entering “<i>Customize your gift</i>” (or the text you entered) into “Requirement”, so that those options are going to be visible only if users check the “<i>Customize your gift</i>” checkbox.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/requirment.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-787158\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-787158\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/requirment.jpg\" alt=\"requirment\" width=\"936\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/requirment.jpg 936w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/requirment-300x64.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/requirment-768x164.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/requirment-382x82.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/requirment-270x58.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 936px) 100vw, 936px\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Destination</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Now you should create a field that will let customers add the shipping address, that&#8217;s why you need to create a “<b>textarea</b>” field and rename it as you see fit, for this tutorial, I picked: “Shipping Address”.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remember to put “Customize your Gift” under Requirement to make this function appear only after clicking the checkbox.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In the Option Label enter the text you wish to display on the side of the option and, if you wish, also the added costs that specific option comes with.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-shipping.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-787149\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-787149\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-shipping.jpg\" alt=\"customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-shipping\" width=\"837\" height=\"304\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-shipping.jpg 837w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-shipping-300x109.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-shipping-768x279.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-shipping-382x139.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-shipping-270x98.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 837px) 100vw, 837px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And that&#8217;s how your product is going to look so far:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-shipping-front.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-787150\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-787150\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-shipping-front.jpg\" alt=\"customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-shipping-front\" width=\"900\" height=\"629\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-shipping-front.jpg 900w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-shipping-front-300x210.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-shipping-front-768x537.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-shipping-front-382x267.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-shipping-front-196x137.jpg 196w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Delivery Times</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">One of the most handy aspects of this kind of service is being able to choose the time slot we prefer, in order to avoid missing the recipient.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">To offer this option, create a “select” option that will offer tour customers the chance to choose between different time slots, in this tutorial I&#8217;ve set three of them:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>7am – 11am</li>\r\n	<li>1pm – 4pm</li>\r\n	<li>5pm – 8pm</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Always remember to put “Customize your Gift” under Requirement to make this function appear only after clicking the checkbox.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In the Option Label field, always add the text you wish to display beside the option and, if you want, the extra cost that options comes with.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-time.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-787151\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-787151\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-time.jpg\" alt=\"customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-time\" width=\"889\" height=\"464\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-time.jpg 889w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-time-300x157.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-time-768x401.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-time-88x45.jpg 88w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-time-382x199.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-time-262x137.jpg 262w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 889px) 100vw, 889px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And this is how your product is going to look so far:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-time-front.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-787152\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-787152\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-time-front.jpg\" alt=\"customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-time-front\" width=\"893\" height=\"659\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-time-front.jpg 893w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-time-front-300x221.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-time-front-768x567.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-time-front-382x282.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-time-front-186x137.jpg 186w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 893px) 100vw, 893px\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Shipping Date</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Customers need to be able to choose the day their bouquet is going to be delivered, so create a “Date” field and add it to the three previous ones.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remember to put “Customize your Gift” under Requirement to make this function appear only after clicking the checkbox.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In the Option Label field, always add the text you wish to display beside the option and, if you want, the extra cost that options comes with.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-date.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-787145\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-787145\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-date.jpg\" alt=\"customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-date\" width=\"889\" height=\"380\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-date.jpg 889w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-date-300x128.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-date-768x328.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-date-382x163.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-date-270x115.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 889px) 100vw, 889px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And this is how your product is going to look so far:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-date-front.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-787146\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-787146\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-date-front.jpg\" alt=\"customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-date-front\" width=\"581\" height=\"440\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-date-front.jpg 581w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-date-front-300x227.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-date-front-382x289.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-date-front-181x137.jpg 181w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 581px) 100vw, 581px\" /></a></p>\r\n<b>Card with a dedication message/ Special Instructions</b>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In both of these cases you can chose the “textarea” field in order for customers to be able to add what they want in the card and also delivery notes.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remember to put “Customize your Gift” under Requirement to make this function appear only after clicking the checkbox.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In the Option Label field, always add the text you wish to display beside the option and, if you want, the extra cost that options comes with.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-greeting.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-787147\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-787147\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-greeting.jpg\" alt=\"customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-greeting\" width=\"828\" height=\"339\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-greeting.jpg 828w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-greeting-300x123.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-greeting-768x314.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-greeting-382x156.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-greeting-270x111.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 828px) 100vw, 828px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And this is how your product is going to look so far:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-greeting-front.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-787148\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-787148\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-greeting-front.jpg\" alt=\"customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-greeting-front\" width=\"572\" height=\"603\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-greeting-front.jpg 572w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-greeting-front-285x300.jpg 285w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-greeting-front-382x403.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-group-types-flowers-greeting-front-130x137.jpg 130w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 572px) 100vw, 572px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Once these parameters are set and their options are saved, these fields are going to appear in the product page.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-view-flower-later.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-787154\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-787154\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-view-flower-later.jpg\" alt=\"customize-product-page-view-flower-later\" width=\"851\" height=\"682\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-view-flower-later.jpg 851w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-view-flower-later-300x240.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-view-flower-later-768x615.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-view-flower-later-382x306.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customize-product-page-view-flower-later-171x137.jpg 171w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 851px) 100vw, 851px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">As you can see the three bouquet sizes are always visible, while in order to see the other options, customers need to click the checkbox:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Preferred-time.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-787157\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-787157\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Preferred-time.jpg\" alt=\"Preferred time\" width=\"921\" height=\"783\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Preferred-time.jpg 921w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Preferred-time-300x255.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Preferred-time-768x653.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Preferred-time-382x325.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Preferred-time-161x137.jpg 161w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 921px) 100vw, 921px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">See?</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In just a few steps you are now able to use your WooCommerce based store to sell and distribute flower arrangements into a much bigger market, thanks <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/docs-plugins/yith-woocommerce-product-add-ons/\">the WooCommerce Product add-ons plugin</a>!</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:128:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/woocommerce-selling-flowers-with-home-delivery-service-and-dedications-like-interflora/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"E-Commerce: Ask for the required information only during the checkout\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:105:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/e-commerce-ask-for-the-required-information-only-during-the-checkout/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:113:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/e-commerce-ask-for-the-required-information-only-during-the-checkout/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 18 Apr 2016 15:01:06 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"https://yithemes.com/?p=786247\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:343:\"Since the process of buying online is so different from the one involved in buying from a physical store, we tend to (wrongly) imply that customers are also different. We don&#8217;t do this consciously: nobody actually believes that customers that buy from online stores are from a different species than real life customers, but we [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Andrea Presenti\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7210:\"<p dir=\"ltr\">Since the process of buying online is so different from the one involved in buying from a physical store, we tend to (wrongly) imply that customers are also different.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">We don&#8217;t do this consciously: nobody actually believes that customers that buy from online stores are from a different species than real life customers, but we do tend to treat them differently without taking into account the fact that they think and act in the same way.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Have you ever really considered the differences between a real life purchase and an online one?</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In real life, we get into store, pick up our item of choice, pay and leave.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Nobody asks us where we live, our cellphone number, name, surname, etc&#8230; that&#8217;s why we need to be careful while asking for our customers&#8217; information during checkout.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Under a psychological perspective, this request could feel like an invasion of somebody&#8217;s privacy or even an attempted scam, that&#8217;s why Jakob Nielsen himself (the web page usability Guru) focused part of his studies on the information we ask our customers during the checkout in particular.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Let&#8217;s go through 6 tips you should follow while asking our customers personal information.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>1) Don&#8217;t ask for more personal data then you need</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Inserting personal data in an online form feels like a gamble to most users, especially on websites we haven&#8217;t bought from before.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">A certain degree of information is obviously required, just try to ask for the required ones only: for instance, if you are selling digital products, the shipping address field is pointless and customers might hesitate to enter it.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">That&#8217;s why it&#8217;s important to carefully pick which information you need: it&#8217;s best to have to ask for more data afterwards, rather then having your customers abandon their cart.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>2) More fields = More mistakes</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Another reason why you should only ask for the strictly required amount of information is to reduce the amount of mistakes on the customer&#8217;s end.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">That&#8217;s why it&#8217;s advisable to divide the checkout process in a few steps: a big page full of fields to fill feels chaotic, tiring and makes it more likely to make mistakes.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The same goes for useless fields: the more fields customers need to fill, the more likely it is that they will get something wrong. And a mistake here might imply one of two things:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Customers need to fill in the form again, which is frustrating and will increase the dropout rate on checkout.</li>\r\n	<li>The data you gathered is wrong and might compromise your sales.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">So for short: the least number of steps customers need to take, the sooner they will reach their goal.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>3) Explain why you need certain information</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Customers don&#8217;t act likethey are computers: they don&#8217;t take your requests as orders and answer them right away. Customers wonder why some personal data is required and what use could you have for that piece of information.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Let&#8217;s make a practical example: you sell products that require shipping using a courier.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">You know for a fact that providing the customers&#8217; phone numbers reduces returns and improves delivery, so you ask for it during the checkout process.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Asking for the phone number during the purchase is a dangerous practice: the average customer associates giving away their phone number to:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Spam calls</li>\r\n	<li>Charges to their phone bills</li>\r\n	<li>Paid subscriptions</li>\r\n	<li>Personal data loss</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This clearly isn&#8217;t your case, but customers may become suspicious and drop out of their purchase.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This will be prevented if you clearly explain why you need that information, since you will answer the question customers might be asking beforehand, thus solving the problem at its roots.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>4) The reason behind some information: The gift</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In case of a gift or surprise, customers might not want to share some of their personal data (such as the phone number) out of fear that the courier/seller might spoil the surprise.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In this case too you should make clear why that information is required, possibly pointing out that it&#8217;s needed in order to make sure the product will reach their owners in time.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Presents are often bought while keeping in mind the delivery times.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>5) Important information? Ask them later!</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Among all of the information you need to ask your customers, some are particularly important for sellers.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Not because they allow shipping and billing, but because they allow you to isolate a behavioral model, thus becoming a fine tool for statistics you can use to improve your sales.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In case you want to gather some kind of information that is not absolutely required during the checkout (and would then seem irrelevant) you are better off presenting your customers with a survey after the purchase.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">That&#8217;s how you will avoid getting quick and useless replies customers would leave just to get rid of some fields and you can get actual data with real statistic value.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">P.S. It would be a good idea to offer discount vouchers in exchange for this kind of information: this will make customers feel more involved in your store and the survey itself will become a way to increase sales!</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>6) If any unusual fields are present, explain why</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Customers who are accustomed to buying online are used to a purchase process that always revolve around the same requirements (personal data, shipping, billing, payment) and the same fields.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">That&#8217;s why finding an unusual field in the checkout process might make customers get suspicious, breaking the good feeling that brought them to purchase in the first place, which can be fatal for your sales.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">That&#8217;s why in case you need to ask for something specific, it&#8217;s always good to ask why: maybe using a link next to a specific field or an icon that would open a popup that explains the reason behind a certain request.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Doing this will make customers feel reassured and move forward with their purchase. It&#8217;s a good idea to insert these explanations in common fields as well: it&#8217;s best to be as clear as possible since customers want to know why they are entering a specific piece of personal information.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Besides, explaining only one field among many others could be counterproductive, since we would be providing only one answer while many other could arise.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">These are six useful steps to offer a checkout process that will rise the conversion rate on your sales. An effective checkout system is a great and useful feature your store should offer.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:110:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/e-commerce-ask-for-the-required-information-only-during-the-checkout/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"WooCommerce Account Settings: Registration options and Endpoints\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:108:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/woocommerce-guide/woocommerce-account-settings-registration-options-and-endpoints/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:117:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/woocommerce-guide/woocommerce-account-settings-registration-options-and-endpoints/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 12 Apr 2016 07:54:39 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"WooCommerce Guide\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"https://yithemes.com/?p=786255\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:357:\"Welcome back to our WooCommerce configuration guide! In the previous chapter I showed you how to configure the shipping options, today I&#8217;m going through the configuration of the “my account” page for your customers. This step is particularly important, since this is the place your customers will spend most of their time and have access [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Andrea Presenti\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6119:\"<p dir=\"ltr\">Welcome back to our WooCommerce configuration guide!</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In the previous chapter I showed you how to configure the shipping options, today I&#8217;m going through the configuration of the “my account” page for your customers.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This step is particularly important, since this is the place your customers will spend most of their time and have access to their orders: a wrong configuration of the “my account” page can damage your store&#8217;s image and your relationship with your customers.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">But don&#8217;t be afraid, it&#8217;s a simple process, and we are just about to see it in detail!</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In order to configure the “my account” page, go to <b>WooCommerce &gt; settings &gt; Account </b>and you will find this screen:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-786260\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woocommerce-settings-account.jpg\" alt=\"woocommerce-settings-account\" width=\"1019\" height=\"626\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woocommerce-settings-account.jpg 1019w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woocommerce-settings-account-300x184.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woocommerce-settings-account-768x472.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woocommerce-settings-account-382x235.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woocommerce-settings-account-223x137.jpg 223w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1019px) 100vw, 1019px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">As you can see, the very first option you should configure is the one that allows you to decide which page is going to work as the “my account” page on your website.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">It is usually automatically generated by the WooCommerce installation, but just in case you need to create it or change it, remember that all you need to do is to create a page and enter the <code>[woocommerce_my_account]</code> in it.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Once you have created the page, you are going to need to set it as “<b>My Account</b>”.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Now you need to set the <b>Endpoints</b> of the page:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-786261\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woocommerce-settings-account-endpoints.jpg\" alt=\"woocommerce-settings-account-endpoints\" width=\"758\" height=\"394\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woocommerce-settings-account-endpoints.jpg 758w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woocommerce-settings-account-endpoints-300x156.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woocommerce-settings-account-endpoints-88x45.jpg 88w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woocommerce-settings-account-endpoints-382x199.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woocommerce-settings-account-endpoints-264x137.jpg 264w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 758px) 100vw, 758px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Endpoints are custom endings for the “My Account” page url that will change according to the user&#8217;s actions.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In the example above, if customers change their address, the address bar url will be:<a href=\"http://www.woocommerceguide.com/my-account/edit-address\"> www.woocommerceguide.com/mio-account/edit-address</a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">You can customize these endpoints however you prefer, just remember that they need to be unique so that they won&#8217;t create conflicts within the page.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Then, you find the <b>Registration Options:</b></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-786262\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woocommerce-settings-account-Registration.jpg\" alt=\"woocommerce-settings-account-Registration\" width=\"729\" height=\"283\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woocommerce-settings-account-Registration.jpg 729w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woocommerce-settings-account-Registration-300x116.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woocommerce-settings-account-Registration-382x148.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/woocommerce-settings-account-Registration-270x105.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 729px) 100vw, 729px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The first field is <b>Enable Registration</b>, where we can find three options:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><b>Enable registration on the “Checkout” page</b> – Allows customers to register directly in the checkout page.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Enable registration on the “My Account” page </b>– When users that are not logged in visit the “My Account” page, they will find the registration fields.</li>\r\n	<li><b>Display returning customer login reminder on the “Checkout” page</b> &#8211; When users that are not logged in reach the checkout page, they will be displayed a message inviting them to log in (but only in case they already bought from your website).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-786256\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Login-reminder.jpg\" alt=\"Login-reminder\" width=\"820\" height=\"430\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Login-reminder.jpg 820w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Login-reminder-300x157.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Login-reminder-768x403.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Login-reminder-88x45.jpg 88w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Login-reminder-382x200.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Login-reminder-261x137.jpg 261w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 820px) 100vw, 820px\" />\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Now you need to set the two final option concerning the <b>Account Creation</b>:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Automatically generate a customer name from the user email</li>\r\n	<li>Automatically generate customer password.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">These two are rather self explanatory.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And this was the last section in this configuration guide about user accounts.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">See you in the next chapter!</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:113:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/woocommerce-guide/woocommerce-account-settings-registration-options-and-endpoints/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:47:\"Email Marketing using WooCommerce and Mailchimp\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:84:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/email-marketing-using-woocommerce-and-mailchimp/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:92:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/email-marketing-using-woocommerce-and-mailchimp/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 11 Apr 2016 11:37:41 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:30:\"https://yithemes.com/?p=785316\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:274:\"There are tools and marketing tips that are in such common use they are now part of our daily lives. What&#8217;s risky in such a massive use of the same tool is to stop seeing it as a tool but just as a common element we all deal with. This happens in the case of [&#8230;]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"Andrea Presenti\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11377:\"<p dir=\"ltr\">There are tools and<a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tag/sales/\"> marketing tips</a> that are in such common use they are now part of our daily lives.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">What&#8217;s risky in such a massive use of the same tool is to stop seeing it as a tool but just as a common element we all deal with.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>This happens in the case of newsletters</strong>: we are so used to see websites inviting us to subscribe to their newsletter that we forget the actual importance of this marketing tool and maybe we don&#8217;t even consider using it for our own store.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Or if we do, we don&#8217;t know how to use its full potential, reducing it simply to a way to spam our products or promotions.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">As I&#8217;ve stated before, a tool is only as good as the hand who uses it, that&#8217;s why today I&#8217;m going to analyze a successful <strong>Email Marketing strategy</strong> you will be able to apply to your own business.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>The protagonist of today&#8217;s article is William</em>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>William&#8217;s Case: More reviews, More sales</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">William&#8217;s case is one of the most fitting in order to show how a good marketing campaign might improve your business.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">William is a web journalist: after spending the past five years writing for blogs and online journals, he decided to offer his experience to others in the form of an Online Writing Course.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">It was a winning idea: as we have seen in previous articles, <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/how-to-offer-a-preview-for-your-learning-courses-audio-and-video/\">offering an online course</a> has several good aspects, including<a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/how-to-increase-the-average-purchase-value-in-your-store/\"> rising the average transaction value</a>, little development costs, and the chance to keep customers loyal to your services.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">William was able to sell his course to many enthusiasts in his field that were able to read his articles before, but clearly that was a limited customer pool.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">After the first months had good sales, the course started to make less and less money, to the point that William wondered if his customer pool had already depleted.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Visit wise, though, many people kept being redirected to his website when looking for a writing course, so why were his sales going down?</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">He considered the possibility that those who were interested in his course were not likely to buy it since it didn&#8217;t have reviews or testimonials, and he was right.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/how-to-encourage-further-purchases-and-increase-the-amount-of-reviews-on-your-e-commerce-store/\">Reviews are very important for any kind of product</a>, but the higher the price, the more customers&#8217; opinion becomes relevant.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">When looking for a learning course then, it&#8217;s important that people who had the same necessities of other possible buyers, display their satisfaction about a certain product.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">So William decided to exploit the <a href=\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/from-woocommerce-to-mailchimp-how-to-use-email-marketing-to-increase-the-conversion-rate-on-your-online-store/\">Email Marketing system</a> in order to increase the number of his reviews, managing to multiply them tenfold thanks to an automated email system.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Email Marketing: Trigger e Follow Up</h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">William used the famous <a href=\"http://mailchimp.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Mailchimp </a><strong>Email Marketing</strong>, he first created a “Customers” group within his Mailchimp mailing list:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-785324\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/group.jpg\" alt=\"group\" width=\"1018\" height=\"701\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/group.jpg 1018w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/group-300x207.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/group-768x529.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/group-382x263.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/group-199x137.jpg 199w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1018px) 100vw, 1018px\" /></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">That&#8217;s how he was able to divide the subscribers between those who subscribed using the form on his website and those who actually purchased his course.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In order to identify this second type of subscriber, William used a plugin that allowed him to set advanced options during the checkout, starting from the group they would end up in:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/mailchimp-plugin.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-785325\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-785325\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/mailchimp-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"mailchimp-plugin\" width=\"1000\" height=\"476\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/mailchimp-plugin.jpg 1000w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/mailchimp-plugin-300x143.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/mailchimp-plugin-768x366.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/mailchimp-plugin-382x182.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/mailchimp-plugin-270x129.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Once the group is set up he had to decide which item should trigger certain customer to end up being part of a specific group:</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/mailchimp-plugin2.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-785326\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-785326\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/mailchimp-plugin2.jpg\" alt=\"mailchimp-plugin2\" width=\"803\" height=\"160\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/mailchimp-plugin2.jpg 803w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/mailchimp-plugin2-300x60.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/mailchimp-plugin2-768x153.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/mailchimp-plugin2-382x76.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/mailchimp-plugin2-270x54.jpg 270w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 803px) 100vw, 803px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And that’s how he identified a specific group of users that bought his writing course among his Mailchimp list. So he could use a much more precise tool that would allow him to contact them at any time, both manually or in an automatic way.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">And that’s exactly what William did: he exploited Mailchimp’s automatic functions.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><a href=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Automation.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-785320\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-785320\" src=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Automation.jpg\" alt=\"Automation\" width=\"1023\" height=\"650\" srcset=\"https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Automation.jpg 1023w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Automation-300x191.jpg 300w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Automation-768x488.jpg 768w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Automation-382x243.jpg 382w, https://yithemes.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Automation-216x137.jpg 216w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1023px) 100vw, 1023px\" /></a></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">For short: William knew his course lasted one month. That&#8217;s why he set an automatic email to be sent to any email address in the “Customers” group, so only those who actually bought the course.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The email was scheduled to be sent exactly 40 days after purchasing the course, in order for customers to have time to complete it and start to apply his new knowledge, but not too long after, which would let customers to forget about it.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">That&#8217;s how he had an email group he could send an email to, once the course was over.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">What then? If he&#8217;d ask for a review right away, very few would have answered&#8230; after all, they&#8217;d had nothing to gain from that.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">He then used another strategy, the email he scheduled only contained a few lines and could be summarized as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><i>Hey, how are you doing today?</i></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><i>Now that you&#8217;ve completed your Writing Course I can&#8217;t wait to see how much your skills have improved!</i></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><i>The best part of an online course is that I can talk to my students even after lessons, so I&#8217;d like to know how did you enjoy my course!</i></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">William purposely used a rather informal and friendly tone for his automatic email, which led his subscribers to believe he was taking personal interest in their progresses, thus becoming a real testimonial magnet!</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Can you tell the difference between that message and this one:</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><i>Hello,</i></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><i>Ten days ago you bought my Writing Course, Thank you!</i></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><i>If you enjoyed it, please leave a review.</i></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><i>Kind Regards,</i></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><i>William</i></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Both emails have the purpose to gather reviews and testimonials, but while William used the first one to put himself in a position of advantage, since he took personal interest in them without (apparently) asking for anything in return, in the second case the request for reviews obscured the rest of the message, making the customer feel just like another one of his sales.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">William&#8217;s ways can be adapted to other kind of stores as well, such as one that deals in several different types of products.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Just create a Mailchimp group and divide it into a few dedicated subcategories. For instance, say I sell books, ebooks and music cds, I can set a rule that specifies that according to the product they bought, customers are going to be inserted in the Customers &gt; Books, Customers &gt; Ebooks or Customers &gt; CD subcategory.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">That&#8217;s how I can divide my emails into categories and create as many rules (also called<strong> Follow Up</strong>) as I want in order to achieve different results.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><em>In William&#8217;s case, for instance, he exploited the Follow Up in order to obtain reviews.</em></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">They can also be used to promote a product that&#8217;s about to be sold (creating a pre-sale marketing campaign) or to sell a second product to a customer that has already bought something from you (maybe including a discount code in the emails).</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">As I stated at the beginning of the article: every tool is just as good as the hand that uses it, so just get your creativity going and allow it to improve your store.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">P.S. If you use WooCommerce,<a href=\"https://yithemes.com/themes/plugins/yith-woocommerce-mailchimp/\"> WooCommerce Mail Chimp</a> is a useful Mail Marketing plugin which allows you to automatically insert your customers&#8217; emails into a specific list or group according to the kind of purchase he performed, if you wish.</p>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:89:\"https://yithemes.com/blog/tutorials/email-marketing-using-woocommerce-and-mailchimp/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:26:\"https://yithemes.com/feed/\";s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateFrequency\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:\"type\";i:128;s:7:\"headers\";a:14:{s:4:\"date\";s:29:\"Sat, 25 Jun 2016 02:47:16 GMT\";s:6:\"server\";s:6:\"Apache\";s:7:\"expires\";s:29:\"Thu, 19 Nov 1981 08:52:00 GMT\";s:13:\"cache-control\";s:62:\"no-store, no-cache, must-revalidate, post-check=0, pre-check=0\";s:6:\"pragma\";s:8:\"no-cache\";s:4:\"etag\";s:34:\"\"fb8f969c2a8f54fe0af2c60079be5d65\"\";s:12:\"x-powered-by\";s:22:\"W3 Total Cache/0.9.4.1\";s:4:\"link\";s:57:\"<https://yithemes.co